To run the Streaming application, the dependencies in the pom.xml file must be added first.

Kafka should then be run using the specified versions.

4 different topics are created on Kafka. Color, illness, odortaste, and unusualstate.

1- Run batch file, save model with any ml aggregation.
2- Add the interface files required for streaming.
3- Before running the realtime file, determine the path to send the test data to Apache Kafka.
4- Run Kafka.
5- Run Realtime.scala, send the appropriate test data to the test folder you specified.
6- Spark directs the information to the name of the relevant topic according to the result obtained from the "prediction" column.
